  "response_text": "Given the sudden increase in fresh fruit prices, opting for frozen or dried alternatives can be a cost-effective way to maintain a healthy diet rich in antioxidants. \n\nOne of the cheapest frozen alternatives is frozen mixed berries, which include a combination of blueberries, strawberries, raspberries, and blackberries. These berries are packed with antioxidants like anthocyanins and vitamin C. A 1-pound (450g) bag of frozen mixed berries can cost between $2 to $3, depending on the store and location.\n\nAs for dried alternatives, dried apricots are a budget-friendly option. They are rich in vitamin A and beta-carotene, which are powerful antioxidants. A 12-ounce (340g) bag of dried apricots can cost between $2 to $4, depending on the brand and quality.\n\nIn comparison, frozen mixed berries are likely to be the absolute cheapest option, with a lower cost per ounce than dried apricots. However, prices may vary depending on your location and the specific store you shop at. It's always a good idea to check prices at different stores to find the best deal.",
